beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Had tried a nice lemon beer at the NW Brewfest, but forgot the name. So when I saw this in the beer aisle at the grocery store, thought I'd pick some up and give it a try. Smells lemon-fruity, taste is more like lemon-infused beer than the traditional fruit beers that I prefer (I prefer the taste of brewed fruit rather than infused fruit). Would probably taste okay on a hot day if there's nothing better to drink.
The Zoo, Lake Union - Seattle: Good solid average beer, does well accompanying games of pool or darts. Well worth upgrading to Fat Tire from Bud, Miller, or Heineken.

Seattle, Bottleworks: The label was screaming cherries, so I picked it up for a trial. This stuff tastes great! Tastes just like cherry soda, only it's beer. Nice cherry red color. Tart like a cherry but finishes nice n smooth.
Pete's Wines, Lake Union - Seattle: Currant flavor is a little tart. Tastes great if you like tart beverages (I do!). Nice color -- looks like a dark champagne. :-)
Pete's Wines, Lake Union - Seattle: Great flavor and aroma. Lambics are a great alternative for those who normally don't care for beer. Nice cherry flavor.

Nice light and fruity beer. I wouldn't categorize this as a "fruit beer" since it's clearly more "beer" tasting than "fruit" (just isn't like my fave lambics, etc.). This is a good choice, however, for someone who might not normally like most beers.

From Top Foods, Lake Tapps: The aroma was delightful -- made me think of an orange creamsicle (oh, days of my youth!). Light and fruity, but a slight orange bitter after bite -- probably due to the orange rind/peel combination -- the bitterness to the drink makes it extra great to sip when it's hot out.
beer_name: Buffalo Bills Orange Blossom Cream Ale

review_blob: On tap at Gordon Biersch, Seattle, Wash.: Looked and smelled refreshing. Goes great with their garlic fries. ;-)
